# Portfolio Website v3 – Architectural Walkthrough

> **Purpose of this document:** This is a comprehensive, structured walkthrough of Ayan Sadhukhan's highly advanced v3 personal portfolio website. Feed this entire document into Gemini and ask it to generate a detailed prompt that can be used with Gemini 3.1 Pro to further analyze or expand this updated portfolio.

---

## 1. Tech Stack & Build System

| Layer | Technology | Details |
|---|---|---|
| **Bundler** | Vite 7.2.4 | Dev server, HMR, production build |
| **Markup** | Vanilla HTML5 | Single [index.html](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/index.html) structure |
| **Styling** | Vanilla CSS | Single [main.css](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/src/styles/main.css) with CSS variables, CRT scanlines, and Light/Dark themes |
| **Interactivity** | Vanilla JS (ES Module) | Single [main.js](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/src/main.js) driving Three.js, IntersectionObservers, and API fetching |
| **Font** | Google Fonts – Inter | Weights: 300, 400, 500, 600, 700 |
| **Hosting** | AWS S3 + CloudFront | Static hosting with CDN and HTTPS |

No React, Vue, or Tailwind. Pure HTML/CSS/JS served directly through Vite. The codebase has been stripped of all unused boilerplate to maximize efficiency.

---

## 2. File Structure

```
Portfolio/
├── index.html              # Single-page HTML (all content + SEO Meta + JSON-LD)
├── package.json            # Vite build scripts
├── bucket-policy.json      # AWS S3 bucket policy
├── cloudfront-config.json  # CloudFront distribution config
└── src/
    ├── main.js             # Core JS: Three.js WebGL, Terminal Emulator, SVG Sparklines, Intersection Flow
    └── styles/
        └── main.css        # Core styles: Design system, CRT scanlines, SVG Animations
```

> **Note:** All default Vite boilerplate ([vite.svg](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/public/vite.svg), [style.css](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/src/style.css), [javascript.svg](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/src/javascript.svg), [counter.js](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/src/counter.js)) has been permanently deleted.

---

## 3. SEO & Accessibility Rigor

- **Meta Tags:** Open Graph (`og:title`, `og:image`, etc.) and Twitter Cards (`twitter:card`) are configured for rich link sharing.
- **Structured Data:** A `<script type="application/ld+json">` block injects a complete `Person` schema, mapping Ayan Sadhukhan to his job, employer (JP Morgan), University (VIT), and relevant skills.
- **Favicon:** Uses an inline SVG data-uri lightning bolt `⚡`.
- **A11y:** A `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` query has been added to [main.css](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/src/styles/main.css). This physically removes the canvas element and disables all custom CSS hover/spin/pulse animations to provide a calm experience for users sensitive to motion.

---

## 4. JS & CSS Core Features

### 4.1 WebGL "Cluster" Visualization (Three.js Hero)
Behind the hero text sits a lightweight, pure-code Three.js scene ([main.js](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/src/main.js)).
- **Design:** Renders a 3D node graph representing a distributed Kubernetes cluster. A subtle Bloom post-processing pass (`EffectComposer`) makes active nodes emit a realistic neon glow against the dark theme.
- **Interaction:** Utilizes custom raycasting. Hovering over a 3D node scales it up, and a pure HTML/CSS tooltip perfectly tracks the mouse in 3D space, displaying mock telemetry (e.g., "Pod: Search-API | Latency: 12ms | Status: Healthy").
- **Performance:** Degrades gracefully via `@media (prefers-reduced-motion)` and halts the `requestAnimationFrame` loop on `visibilitychange` (when the tab is backgrounded).

### 4.2 The "Data Pipeline" Scroll Flow
A continuous flow of data guides the user down the page from top to bottom.
- **Design:** A complex absolute SVG `<path>` weaves precisely through the Experience, Skills, and Projects sections.
- **Animation:** Uses vanilla JS and `IntersectionObserver` to animate the `stroke-dashoffset` in real-time syncing with the user's scroll position.
- **Packets:** Glowing `<circle>` SVGs dynamically travel down the path utilizing `getPointAtLength` as sections intersect the viewport.

### 4.3 The "Quake-Style" Terminal Overlay
A hidden, functional CLI is built directly into the DOM to highlight engineering prowess.
- **Interaction:** Drops down from the top of the screen via a CSS transform when the user presses backtick (\`) or `Ctrl + K`.
- **Design:** Styled with a subtle CRT scanline linear gradient, green monospace font, and a keyframe-driven blinking block cursor.
- **Commands:** A comprehensive switch-statement parser handles commands (with Up/Down arrow history): `help`, `theme --toggle`, `cat resume.txt`, `fetch leetcode` (with simulated async delays), and `status`.

### 4.4 Client-Side "Telemetry" Dashboard (SVG Sparklines)
Located right below the Skills section, analyzing GitHub activity dynamically without bulky charting dependencies.
- **Data Integration:** Fetches `api.github.com/users/ayan2809/repos`, aggregating `stargazers_count` and `size` data chronologically. Implements `sessionStorage` caching (1-hour TTL) to prevent rate limits.
- **Visualization:** A vanilla JS layout engine generates smooth, Catmull-Rom approximated quadratic bezier SVG curves (`Q`) on the fly. Utilizes CSS `stroke-dashoffset` for an intricate draw-in animation with an opacity gradient fill.

### 4.2 Seamless Light/Dark Mode Toggle
- **UI:** A custom button in the navigation bar interpolates between a Sun and Moon SVG using CSS opacity and rotation transforms.
- **State Mgmt ([main.js](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/src/main.js)):** Checks `localStorage` or `window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: light)')` on load and applies a `[data-theme="light"]` attribute to the `<html>` root.
- **CSS ([main.css](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/src/styles/main.css)):** The default root variables dictate the Dark theme. The Light theme swaps out `--bg-primary`, `--text-primary`, and box-shadow variables while retaining the custom accent indigo/cyan gradients.
- **Transitioning:** A global `--transition-colors` ensures that switching from dark to light triggers a smooth 400ms crossfade across the entire application interface.

### 4.3 Code-Based SVG Animations
Standard emojis in the Experience, Education, and Contact sections were replaced with pristine, inline `<svg>` elements.
- **Styling:** CSS classes define scalable strokes (`stroke: var(--text-primary)`).
- **Hover Micro-interactions:**
  - `.icon-animated`: Base class causing a 1.1x scale and a stroke color transition to the primary accent color.
  - `.icon-pulse`: Triggers an infinite `@keyframes svg-pulse` scaling effect (e.g., the analytics graph icon).
  - `.icon-float`: Triggers a 3s `@keyframes svg-float` hovering effect (e.g., the robot context engineering icon).
  - `.icon-spin`: Triggers a continuous 360-degree `@keyframes svg-spin` (e.g., the rocket performance optimization icon).

### 4.4 Optimized Scroll Listeners
The sticky nav highlighting and parallax hero effect rely on `window.pageYOffset`. In [main.js](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/src/main.js), this scroll listener is wrapped tightly inside a `requestAnimationFrame` throttle, preventing forced synchronous layouts and keeping the site locked at 60fps even under heavy scrolling.

---

## 5. Page Sections (in order)

The portfolio navigates linearly via smooth-scrolling anchor links. Highlights include:

### Hero
- Interactive canvas background.
- Parallax: Text translates up and drops opacity on scroll.
- Entrance Animation: High-performance CSS `@keyframes entranceFadeUp` tied to CSS variables (`--stagger: 1`, `--stagger: 2`) orchestrates a staggered slide-in load sequence for the intro text.

### About & Experience
- Detailed text establishing Ayan as a Backend Engineer at JPMorgan serving 18M+ users. Specializes in scalable backend architectures (AWS Lambda/S3/OpenSearch).
- 6 highlight cards (API Development, Scalable System Design, Context Engineering, Performance Optimization, Cloud-Native, Observability) utilizing the new, custom animated SVGs.

### Skills & Certifications
- Tag-based grid covering Python, Java, AWS, Kubernetes, OpenSearch, etc.
- Responsive flex cards for three AWS certifications linking to Credly (Developer Associate, Solutions Architect Associate, and Machine Learning Specialty).

### Projects & Open Source (Dynamic Content)
1. **GitHub Pinned Repos (Dynamic):** [main.js](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/src/main.js) hits `api.github.com/users/ayan2809/repos` directly. It filters public, non-forked repos, sorts by `stargazers_count`, and maps the top 3 into responsive CSS cards. Renders repo name, description, primary language, stars, and forks cleanly. Includes a `repo-error` fallback linking to GitHub if the fetch fails (or hits a rate limit).
2. **QuesGen (Static):** The featured hackathon-winning application remains highlighted below the GitHub grid.

### Achievements & Education
- Timeline list tracking hackathon wins (Hackatra, Hack36) and the Amazon ML Summer School.
- Education block detailing VIT Chennai (CGPA 9.01/10).

### Contact (Form & Links)
- **Direct Links:** Responsive grid for Email, GitHub, LinkedIn, and LeetCode (all utilizing custom SVG icon hover animations).
- **Contact Form UI:** Beautiful static HTML form requiring Name, Email, and Message.
- **Contact Form Mock ([main.js](file:///Volumes/Projects/Portfolio/src/main.js)):** Intercepts submit, swaps button to an SVG spinner, waits 1.5 seconds, then displays a green success state to simulate backend connectivity. (Currently poised to be wired into AWS API Gateway + Lambda + SES).

